FT  03 AUG 94 / Observer: People's choice
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Karl Habsburg, the grandson of the last ruler of the Austro-Hungarian
empire, is to stand as a candidate in Austria's general election on October
9. Habsburg, 33, who used to host a games show on Austrian television called
'Who is Who?', will stand as an independent candidate on the conservative
People's Party ticket.
Habsburg is also planning to stand as a candidate in Austria's European
elections, expected in May or June next year. Austria will join the European
Union in January. If successful, he will join his father, Otto von Habsburg,
who is a German member of the European parliament.
