FT  03 AUG 94 / Letters to the Editor: A little introspection in order
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr A H HAMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, I was surprised and dismayed that a journal with the reputation and
status of the FT should give space to the silly and bigoted views expressed
by Michael Thompson-Noel (Hawks and Handsaws, July 23/24) about 'people from
the regions' (is not the south-east a region?). I suggest a little quiet
introspective research would be appropriate before he applies the expression
'micro-brained' to others.
A H Hampson,
