<HEADLINE>
FT  02 AUG 94 / International Capital Markets: Cigna registers 53% gain in
second-quarter income
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Cigna, the US insurance group, continued to record strong advances in its
second-quarter health insurance business, though the costs of meeting
property/casualty claims rose.
Overall, net income saw a better-than-expected 53 per cent rise to Dollars
135m. Earnings per share were Dollars 1.86, up from Dollars 1.22.
The advance was led by health maintenance organisation (HMO) operations,
which lifted operating income to Dollars 50m from Dollars 32m. The number of
members in HMOs owned by Cigna was a fifth higher at 3.1m. Operating income
from other indemnity insurance rose 11 per cent to Dollars 80m.
Property/casualty operations showed an operating loss of Dollars 32m from
asbestos and environmental claims. But this was more than offset by falling
losses in other property/casualty operations, which dropped two-thirds to
Dollars 35m.
First-half net income rose to Dollars 249m, or Dollars 3.44 a share, from
Dollars 134m, or Dollars 1.86.
</TEXT>
