<HEADLINE>
FT  02 AUG 94 / Observer: Imperial future
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fresh evidence of US cultural imperialism. A colleague using a US computer
software package was surprised to find that the spellcheck programme queried
the existence of the BBC and suggested as a preferred replacement, NBC. . .
.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>USZ  United States of America.
</CN>
<XX>
