<HEADLINE>
FT  02 AUG 94 / Observer: Grave return
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Betting on celebrity deaths is a bigger sport than Observer realised. Since
yesterday's note concerning the New York commodity traders who wager on the
Great Beyond, the postbag has been brimming with regional variations. An
English version 'differing in matters of taste and concern for fair play' is
proving popular at a merchant bank in London which for some reason asks to
remain nameless.
Inclusion of the Queen Mum is off limits, of course, and it goes without
saying that no money is involved. 'One plays the game for its own sake.' But
the Death List does come in handy as a benchmark against which to measure
in-house funds' performance in emerging markets. Last year, it was at one
stage returning a healthy 12 per cent, but 1994 has been a dog. The only hit
has been Kim Il-Sung.
