<TEXT>
Sir, Clement Crisp's otherwise excellent suggestions smack too much of
elitism ('The decline and fall of elegance', July 18). May I suggest two
simple changes to provide a little more democracy:
To balance the evening dress which would be mandatory elsewhere, all those
in the amphitheatre would be required to wear boiler suits and cloth caps.
As a concession to the elitists, tiaras could be issued to the occupants of
boxes.
To ensure absolute equity within the selected dress zones, purchasers of
tickets would be issued with standard regulated dress appropriate to their
zone on arrival at the theatre, the Crush Bar being set aside for changing
purposes.
