<HEADLINE>
FT  02 AUG 94 / People: Cornford hopes insight pays off
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mike Cornford, recently departed head of global foreign exchange at Natwest
Markets, is now running a currency management group called Currency Insight.
The new business, which is in the process of being set up, will focus on
short-term trading strategies, offering investors a low risk, moderate style
of return, rather than the high risk strategies often pursued by hedge
funds.
Currency Insight is backed by Dawnay Day, a small merchant bank. It will
also be working in conjunction with Chilton Capital, a forex consultancy
group, which will assist in raising funds.
Cornford said he would primarily be trying to attract funds from an
institutional base. His marketing pitch is to offer investment managers
access to 25 years' experience as an interbank trader in the foreign
exchange market - the perspective, as he calls it, of a 'fly on the wall of
a dealing room. . . I strongly believe there is a real demand for somebody
who is closedly identified with the day-to-day comments in the marketplace.'
He said the timing of his venture was opportune becausethe volatility of
financial markets this year, often at odds with perceived economic
fundamentals, had forced fund managers to be less dogmatic about their
investment strategies.
</TEXT>
