FT  02 AUG 94 / Franchise system legal aid launched
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
About a quarter of legal-aid services in England and Wales will be provided
through the Legal Aid Board's new franchising operation, it was announced at
the scheme's official launch yesterday.
Mr Stephen Orchard, the board's chief executive, said about 1,000
solicitors' offices had had their applications to become franchisees
accepted.
Under the scheme, firms of solicitors which meet performance and management
criteria are awarded franchises by the board for particular areas of legally
aided work.
The scheme is intended to improve the delivery of legal services, but has
been criticised by some in the profession for being over-rigid in its
control and likely to undermine the freedom of solicitors to conduct cases
as they think best.
