<HEADLINE>
FT  02 AUG 94 / World Trade News: Indonesia to upgrade airports
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JAKARTA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Indonesia plans to boost trade links with neighbouring Malaysia, Brunei and
the Philippines by upgrading airports and ports in Sulawesi and Kalimantan
islands to international standards, Reuter reports from Jakarta. 'The
airports and ports in the two islands will be upgraded to accommodate bigger
planes and ships,' said an official from the Co-ordinating Ministry for
Industry and Trade, adding that the expanded airports would serve
international routes to Asia, the US and Europe.
The ministry earlier said the Sepinggan airport in Balikpapan, East
Kalimantan, would be upgraded with Japanese funding. Japan's Overseas
Economic Co-operation Fund would provide Dollars 150m for the project while
Dollars 125m would come from the Asian Development Bank for the expansion of
the Sam Ratulangi airport in Manado, Sulawesi.
